    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>July 3&#47;53</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I have read your letter<lb/> with much interest&#44; and sincerely thank<lb/> you for it. Your remarks I receive<lb/> with entire respect. When you come to<lb/> see the use I have made of the infor&#45;<lb/>mation you have given me&#44; and of<lb/> what I find in your article in the<lb/> &#8220;History of all the Religious Denominations<lb/> in the <placeName>U.S.</placeName>&#8221; you will not&#44; I think&#44;<lb/> believe that I have any prejudice<lb/> or unkind feelings towards the Jews.<lb/> Far from it.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Had I time to write<lb/> to you at length&#44; or if you had time<lb/> to read some auto<add>&#63;</add> essays&#44;<lb/> I flatter myself that I could con&#45;<lb/>vince a man of your candor<lb/> that some things in your letter are<lb/> incorrect. Should you visit this<lb/> city</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>City it will be sincere pleasure to see<lb/> you. When your translation of the<lb/> Bible comes to be published I hope<lb/> to see it.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">If you embraced <persName>Jesus Christ</persName><lb/> as your Messiah I could feel more<lb/> closely bound to you by friendship&#44;<lb/> but still&#44; claiming toleration&#44; I freely<lb/> accord it to others. Happy to join<lb/> with my Jewish friends in their ad&#45;<lb/><add>&#63;</add> of the Old Testament I wish<lb/> they could with me enjoy the New.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">With much respect&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">I remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">Your&#39;s truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Levi Tappan</persName></p>
			<p>Rev</p>
			<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phila</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
